YAML version <pre>
name: String
game: String
...
autoscaling:
  enabled: true
  min: 1
  max: 10
  policy:
    type: roomOccupancy
    parameters:
      roomOccupancy:
        readyTarget: 0.5
        </pre> JSON version <pre>
{
  "autoscaling": {
    "enabled": true,
    "min": 10,
    "max": 300,
    "policy": {
      "type": "roomOccupancy",
      "parameters": {
        "roomOccupancy": {
          "readyTarget": 0.5
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
        </pre> <p>Below are some simulated examples of how the room occupancy policy will behave:</p> <p>Note that the autoscaling decision will always be limited by the min-max values! .</p> totalRooms occupiedRooms readyTarget desiredNumberOfRooms autoscalingDecision 100 80 0.5 160 Scale Up: +60 100 50 0.5 100 Do Nothing: 0 100 30 0.5 60 Scale Down: -40 50 40 0.3 58 Scale Up: +8 50 35 0.3 50 Do Nothing: 0 50 10 0.3 15 Scale Down: -35 10 5 0.9 50 Scale Up: +40 10 1 0.9 10 Do Nothing: 0 10 1 0.8 5 Scale Down: -5 5 5 0.1 6 Scale Up: +1 1 1 0.3 2 Scale Up: +1 2 2 0.9 20 Scale Up: +18
